  "texts": [
    "In the final step, we apply the inverse DFT to each modified y wm, collect the resulting vectors to form a matrix X wm, and then apply the inverse standardization followed by the inverse YJT to map it back into the original domain.",
    "For discrete features, we round values to the nearest valid entry.",
    "For example, a value of 0.4 for the \"sex\" entry would be rounded to 0 (female), while 0.6 would be rounded to 1 (male).",
    "For bounded features, we clip values to stay within the valid range.",
    "The full procedure is summarized in Algorithm 1."
  ],
